  "@graph": [
    {
      "@id": "m2:M2_GenericConcepts",
      "@type": "owl:Ontology",
      "dcterms:title": "TSCG M2 GenericConcepts Ontology",
      "dcterms:description": "Second layer of the TSCG framework. Defines transdisciplinary GenericConcepts emerging from tensor products of M3 ASFID/REVOI dimensions. M2 is restricted to patterns valid across ALL knowledge fields without exception. KnowledgeField-specific concepts (KnowledgeFieldConcept, KnowledgeField, KnowledgeFieldGenericCombo) are defined in M1. Introduces N-ary polarity framework, GenericConceptCombos (synergistic combinations via ⊗ⁿ⇒ with lattice-join dimension contraction), and bicephalous Eagle Eye (ASFID) / Sphinx Eye (REVOI) dual perspectives.",
      "dcterms:creator": "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI",
      "dcterms:created": "2026-01-14",
      "dcterms:modified": "2026-03-13",
      "owl:versionInfo": "15.11.0",
      "owl:imports": [
        "M3_GenesisSpace.jsonld"
      ],
      "m2:bicephalousArchitecture": {
        "description": "M2 GenericConcepts emerge from tensorization of M3 dimensions. M3 has bicephalous architecture: Eagle Eye (ASFID Territory-Space) for measurement + Sphinx Eye (REVOI Map-Space) for interpretation.",
        "eagleEye": {
          "@id": "m3:eagle_eye:EagleEye",
          "rdfs:seeAlso": "M3_EagleEye.jsonld",
          "dcterms:documentation": {
            "@id": "M3_EagleEye.jsonld",
            "dcterms:format": "application/ld+json",
            "dcterms:type": "Ontology"
          },
          "role": "Territory-Space measurement (ASFID basis)",
          "usage": "M2 tensor formulas use ASFID dimensions (A, S, F, I, D)"
        },
        "sphinxEye": {
          "@id": "m3:sphinx_eye:SphinxEye",
          "rdfs:seeAlso": "M3_SphinxEye.jsonld",
          "dcterms:documentation": {
            "@id": "M3_SphinxEye.jsonld",
            "dcterms:format": "application/ld+json",
            "dcterms:type": "Ontology"
          },
          "role": "Map-Space interpretation (REVOI basis - PROPOSED)",
          "usage": "Future: M2 genericConcepts may have REVOI characterization for Map quality"
        }
      },
      "rdfs:seeAlso": "docs/M2_GenericConcepts_README.md",
      "dcterms:documentation": {
        "@id": "docs/M2_GenericConcepts_README.md",
        "dcterms:format": "text/markdown",
        "dcterms:type": "Documentation"
      },
      "rdfs:comment": "M2 layer constructs genericConcepts through tensorization of M3 ASFID dimensions from Eagle Eye (Territory-Space). Bicephalous architecture: Eagle Eye measures phenomena (ASFID), Sphinx Eye interprets models (REVOI proposed). Each genericConcept is characterized by its tensor formula, category, epistemic gap, and polarity.",
      "m2:tensorSpace": "T_M2 = ⨂_{k=1}^3 H_M3^{ ⊗ k}",
      "m3:ontologyCategory": {
        "@id": "m3:GenericConcepts"
      },
      "m2:totalComponents": 155,
      "m2:componentBreakdown": {
        "order1": 5,
        "order2": 25,
        "order3": 125
      },
      "m2:epistemicGapFormula": "δ(M) = ||P(Reality) - Model|| ∈ [0,1]",
      "m2:polarityPrinciple": "N-ary polarity framework: neutral (N=1), dual (N=2), ternary (N=3), quaternary (N=4), pentagonal (N=5), or general N-ary (N>5). Binary dual is most common case but not exclusive. Hybrid polarity: simultaneous fusion of ASFID (Territory) and REVOI (Map) in single genericConcept through tensor product coupling. Polarity describes intrinsic multiplicity of genericConcept manifestation.",
      "m2:categoryTheory": {
        "m2:functor_tensorization": "F_ ⊗ : Cat_M3 → Cat_M2",
        "m2:functor_instantiation": "F_inst: Cat_M2 → Cat_M1",
        "m2:morphism_inclusion": "↪ (e.g., Homeostasis ↪ Regulation)",
        "m2:morphism_composition": "∘ (e.g., Learning = Memory ∘ Adaptation)",
        "m2:morphism_duality": "op (e.g., Divergence = Convergence^op)",
        "m2:morphism_emergence": "⇒ (e.g., multiple ⇒ emergent)"
      },
      "m2:criticalDecisions": {
        "m2:time_external": "Time is parameter in M3, not 6th dimension. Temporal genericConcepts (Memory, Process) require integration → M2",
        "m2:memory_is_m2": "M(t) = ∫(D - F)dρ requires temporal integration, hence M2 not M3",
        "m2:regulation_is_m2": "A → S → F coupling required, hence M2 not M3",
        "m2:flow_is_m3": "F is 3rd dimension with axiom F ≠ 0.1, not M2 genericConcept",
        "m2:axes_removed_v8": "Triple axes framework (Model/Reality, Analytical/Constructive, Composition/Decomposition) removed. Replaced by: Map-Territory distinction documented as theoretical foundation (see TSCG_Map_Territory_Theoretical_Foundation.md). Composition/Decomposition promoted to dual genericConcepts.",
        "m2:nary_polarity_adopted_v13": "N-ary polarity framework adopted in v13.0.0. Replaces binary restriction. Polarity represents intrinsic multiplicity: neutral (N=1), dual (N=2), ternary (N=3), quaternary (N=4), pentagonal (N=5), N-ary (N>5). Examples: Switch (N-ary states), Mode (N-ary operational categories), Polarity genericConcept itself (N-ary value poles).",
        "m2:purity_principle": "M2 uses pure vocabulary (Ontology, Systems Theory, Cybernetics) - no domain-specific terms. Domain concepts belong to M1 extensions."
      },
      "m2:mathematicalValidationStatus": {
        "m2:status": "preliminary",
        "m2:validatedBy": "Claude (Anthropic LLM)",
        "m2:validationDate": "2026-01-15",
        "m2:requiresExpertReview": true,
        "m2:reviewAreas": [
          "Tensor product correctness",
          "Dirac notation usage",
          "Category theory morphisms",
          "Dimensional coherence",
          "Third-party validation (human experts, other LLMs)"
        ]
      },
      "m2:progress": {
        "m2:genericConceptsDefined": 90,
        "m2:genericConceptsTotal": 90,
        "m2:completionPercentage": 100,
        "m2:neutralPolarity": 59,
        "m2:dualPolarity": 19,
        "m2:naryPolarity": 1,
        "m2:hybridPolarity": 4,
        "totalConcepts": 84,
        "comboConcepts": 4,
        "atomicConcepts": 80
      },
      "m2:changelog": {
        "v15_11_0": {
          "date": "2026-03-23",
          "session": "Ranaora & Yii poclet analysis — TSCG M2 architectural discoveries",
          "source": "DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.19160047",
          "changes": [
            "NEW ATOMIC: m2:Processor (Dynamic, S⊗I⊗F⊗D, neutral) — generic transformer",
            "NEW ATOMIC: m2:Transducer (Energetic, F⊗S⊗I, neutral, subClassOf Processor) — flux converter",
            "NEW ATOMIC: m2:Entropy (Energetic, F⊗I⊗D, dual Entropy/Negentropy) — irreversibility measure (Feynman)",
            "NEW ATOMIC: m2:Stase (Structural, S⊗A, neutral) — F=0 reversible ground state",
            "NEW ATOMIC: m2:Coherence (Structural, A⊗S⊗I⊗R⊗O, dual Coherence/Incoherence, bicephalous) — structural+perceptual alignment",
            "NEW COMBO: m2:Inertia (⊗⇒(Memory,Entropy), S⊗F⊗I⊗D, neutral) — thermodynamic resistance via accumulated Entropy",
            "NEW COMBO: m2:Potentialization (⊗⇒(Activation,Process), A⊗D⊗F, dual +/-) — F=0↔F_active transition",
            "NEW COMBO: m2:AbsorbingState (⊗⇒(Stase,Entropy), S⊗A⊗F⊗I⊗D, neutral) — irreversibly sealed Stase",
            "NEW COMBO: m2:TopologicalDefect (⊗⇒(Incoherence,Invariant), S⊗A⊗I⊗R⊗O, neutral) — locally stable incoherence",
            "REVISED: m2:Dissipation — subClassOf Transducer, produces Entropy, Feynman note (equations are time-reversible)",
            "ARCHITECTURAL M3: F axiom relaxed F≥0 (F=0=Stase valid). F_morphic annotation (F∈Mor∩Ob). F_potential/F_active spectrum. F_total conservation as emergent M2 property.",
            "RECONCILIATION: Coherence^op=Entropy (v6.5.0) was imprecise. Correct: Incoherence→[Dissipation]→Entropy (causal morphism, not categorical dual). Coherence^op=Incoherence; Entropy^op=Negentropy.",
            "Atomics 75→80, Combos 0→4, Total 75→84, neutralPolarity 53→59, dualPolarity 16→19, hybridPolarity 3→4"
          ]
        },
        "v15_10_1": {
          "date": "2026-03-13",
          "changes": [
            "RESTORED: m2:GenericConceptCombo as owl:Class (subClassOf m2:GenericConcept) — instances moved to M1_CoreConcepts.jsonld",
            "NEW CLASS: m2:KnowledgeFieldConceptCombo (subClassOf m2:GenericConceptCombo) — cross-knowledge-field combos",
            "ARCHITECTURE: M2 defines Combo classes only; M1_CoreConcepts hosts all instances"
          ]
        },
        "v15_10_0": {
          "date": "2026-03-13",
          "changes": [
            "ARCHITECTURE: Combo family (8 concepts) migrated to M1_CoreConcepts.jsonld v2.0.0 as m1core:TransdisciplinaryCombo",
            "NEW CONCEPT: m2:Layer (Structural, S⊗I⊗A⊗R, rdfs:subClassOf m2:Segmentation)",
            "NEW CONCEPT: m2:Context (Ontological, O⊗R⊗Im⊗E, pure Map, rdfs:subClassOf m2:Environment)",
            "M2 is now strictly atomic: 75 GenericConcepts across 9 families"
          ]
        },
        "v15_9_0": {
          "date": "2026-02-28",
          "description": "Added m2:Duplication (Dynamic, S⊗I⊗F⊗D⊗V, subClassOf Process). Added m2:Propagation (Combo, ⊗⇒(Cascade,Duplication,Network), S⊗I⊗A⊗D⊗F⊗V⊗Im, 7D). Added m2:Narration (Combo, ⊗⇒(Transformation,Representation,Relation), S⊗I⊗D⊗F⊗V⊗R⊗A⊗Im, 8D — richest Combo). Bifurcation updated: rdfs:subClassOf m2:Duplication (semantic). Dynamic 14→15. Combo 6→8. dualPolarity 14→16. neutralPolarity 52→53. Total 78→81."
        }
      },
