          "Economics: Monetary policy (credit expansion/contraction), fiscal multipliers",
          "Immunology: Clonal expansion (antibody production), immunosuppression",
          "Neuroscience: Synaptic potentiation (LTP), depression (LTD)",
          "Physics: Field amplification (resonance), electromagnetic shielding (attenuation)"
        ],
        "validatedDomains": 10,
        "transdisciplinaryStrength": "Universal - All systems with flows/signals require gain control mechanisms"
      },
      "dcterms:created": "2026-01-31",
      "dcterms:creator": "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI",
      "m2:discoveryContext": "Required for VSM modeling of variety management (S2 amplification, S3 attenuation). Emerges as fundamental dual operation for controlling flow magnitude. Observable in Territory (Ft → D → It: measurable flux, dynamics, information) AND representable in Map (R → O: symbolizable, observable stages). Essential prerequisite for M1_VSM concepts VarietyAmplification and VarietyAttenuation which combine with ValueSpace. Third hybrid genericConcept after Domain and ValueSpace.",
      "m2:hasAttribute": {
        "direction": {
          "@type": "m2:ValueSpace",
          "m2:valueType": "Discrete symbolic",
          "m2:description": "Direction of magnitude change: amplification (gain>1), attenuation (gain<1), or unity (gain=1)",
          "m2:possibleValues": [
            {
              "value": "Amplifying",
              "description": "Gain > 1, increase in magnitude",
              "formula": "G > 1",
              "examples": [
                "Op-amp (voltage gain = 100)",
                "Enzymatic cascade (substrate multiplication)",
                "VSM S2 variety amplification",
                "Optical amplifier (LASER)",
                "Audio amplifier"
              ],
              "characteristics": "Output > Input, energy/signal boost"
            },
            {
              "value": "Attenuating",
              "description": "0 < Gain < 1, decrease in magnitude",
              "formula": "0 < G < 1",
              "examples": [
                "Resistor network (voltage divider)",
                "Optical filter (absorption)",
                "VSM S3 variety attenuation",
                "Sound dampening material",
                "Low-pass filter"
              ],
              "characteristics": "Output < Input, energy/signal reduction"
            },
            {
